# SirHENRY Branding

## Naming Rules
- **Platform name:** SirHENRY (one word, HENRY in caps)
- **AI advisor:** Sir Henry (two words, title case)
- **In code identifiers:** `sirhenry` (lowercase), `SirHenry` (PascalCase), `sir_henry` (snake_case)
- **In user-facing copy:** "SirHENRY" for the platform, "Sir Henry" for the AI persona

## Prohibited Names
- "Family Finance Platform" — NEVER use this anywhere
- "Family Finance & Tax Platform" — NEVER use this
- "family finance" in any form in user-facing strings
- "Henry Financial" as a standalone product name (reserved for legal entity only)

## Where to Check
When creating or modifying any file, ensure these contexts use correct branding:
- Plaid `client_name` configuration
- AI system prompts (chat, categorization, reports)
- Email/notification templates
- Report footers and headers
- README and documentation
- HTML `<title>` tags and meta descriptions
- API response messages that surface to users

## Brand Voice (see docs/BRAND.md for full guide)
- Confident, clear, warm — like a smart friend who's great with money
- Use "you" and "your" — never "the user"
- Use specific numbers — "$1.2M by 55" not "a comfortable retirement"
- Never guilt or preach about spending
